fields.description:
String#toLowerCase()/toUpperCase() without a locale argument can occur unexpected behavior based on the locale. It's written in [Javadoc|http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#toLowerCase()]:
{quote}
For instance, "TITLE".toLowerCase() in a Turkish locale returns "t\u0131tle", where '\u0131' is the LATIN SMALL LETTER DOTLESS I character
{quote}

This issue is derived from HADOOP-10101.

